#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:1
msgid "Make package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:6
msgid ""
"A Make package provides support to easily invoke [GNU Make][gnu-make] "
"commands at various stages of a package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:13
msgid ""
"Make-based projects by default will invoke the default target during the "
"build stage, and invoke the `install` target for the installation stage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:16
msgid ""
"The following shows the default arguments used in stages and outlines "
"configuration options that are available for a Make package to set. See "
"also the [Make package examples](/examples/examples-make). All stages are"
" invoked with a [`PKG_BUILD_DIR`](env-pkg-build-dir) working directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:26
msgid "Configuration stage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:29
msgid ""
"Default configurations for make packages will not run a configuration "
"stage. However, if a user wants to run a specific target during this "
"stage, a target can be added into the configuration options. For example,"
" if the Makefile configuration has a target `prework` that should be "
"invoked during the configuration stage, the following can be used:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:41
msgid "Which will invoke `make` with the arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:47
msgid ""
"Alternatively, if no configuration options are specified, a "
"`<package>-configure` [script](pkg-type-script) can be invoked if "
"available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:56
msgid "Build stage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:59
msgid "The build stage invokes `make` with the arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:65
msgid ""
"This will trigger the default target for the Makefile configuration. "
"Developers can configure a specific target to invoke during the build "
"stage by specifying a [`LIBFOO_BUILD_OPTS`](pkg-opt-make-build-opts) "
"configuration. For example, if a package uses the target `release` for "
"standard release builds, the following can be used:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:77
msgid ""
"The number of jobs is populated by either the [`--jobs` argument](arg-"
"jobs), [`LIBFOO_FIXED_JOBS`](pkg-opt-fixed-jobs) or [`LIBFOO_MAX_JOBS"
"`](pkg-opt-max-jobs). Although, if the configuration results in a single "
"job, the argument will not be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:88
msgid "Install stage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:91
msgid "The install stage invokes `make` with an `install` target:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:97
msgid "With the following environment variables set:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:103
msgid ""
"The `DESTDIR` path will be set to the target sysroot the package should "
"install into (see also [`LIBFOO_INSTALL_TYPE`](pkg-opt-install-type)). "
"`make install` may be invoked multiple times for each target it needs to "
"install into."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:108
msgid ""
"If a package defines install options, the `install` target is not "
"provided by default. Developers can override what target to invoke by "
"adding it into the install options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-make.md:118
msgid ""
"The installation stage can be skipped by configuring "
"[`LIBFOO_MAKE_NOINSTALL`](pkg-opt-make-noinstall)."
msgstr ""

